			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Once you have a fleet of 40 dooms, at the beginning of every turn, remove 39 of them.  If there is a null before the end of the turn you get your fleet back at 40 dooms plus you get an extra 39 dooms.  Now if the null message doesn't happen before the last 20 seconds of your turn, be sure to put them back into the fleet so you can try again next turn.<br />
<br />
It's a cheap tactic, but I believe that others are using it so I thought I'd publish it here so that everyone knows about it and can use it for themselves (if that is what they think is fun anyway).  I haven't tried this yet, but it makes sense from what you have described.<br />
<br />
BTW - until the bug gets fixed, this should work with any ships, not just fleets of 40 dooms.			   <P align=right></P>
